<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Total body length ranged between 10.0 and 11.5 mm. Tail 27.8-35.0% of body length. Hooks 6-8. Anterior teeth 9-10 and posterior teeth 12-20, respectively. Rigid and opaque body (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. A Ferosagitta robusta (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704202" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">18</figureCitation>
). Head wide as neck, roughly round or square shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. A Ferosagitta robusta (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704202" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">18A</figureCitation>
). Grasping spines gently curved and not serrated edge of hooks (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Grasping spine A abruptly curved hooks (Krohnitta subtilis, Krohnittidae) B gently curved and not serrated hooks (Ferosagitta robusta, Sagittidae) C gently curved and serrated hooks (Serratosagitta pacifica, Sagittidae)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704192" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">8B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Number and shape of dentition A Ferosagitta robusta (two rows) B Krohnitta subtilis (one row)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704193" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">9A</figureCitation>
). Teeth short and firm (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Number and shape of dentition A Ferosagitta robusta (two rows) B Krohnitta subtilis (one row)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704193" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">9A</figureCitation>
). 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“B”">&quot;B&quot;</normalizedToken>
shaped eyes had 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“T”">&quot;T&quot;</normalizedToken>
shaped eye pigments (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. A Ferosagitta robusta (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704202" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">18B</figureCitation>
). Collarette on neck (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Number and shape of dentition A Ferosagitta robusta (two rows) B Krohnitta subtilis (one row)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704193" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">9A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. A Ferosagitta robusta (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704202" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">18A</figureCitation>
). Anterior fins 22.4% of body length. Anterior fins beginning just at posterior of ventral ganglion. Starting points of anterior fins 33.1% and ending points of anterior fins 56.5% of body length, respectively (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. A Ferosagitta robusta (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704202" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">18A, D</figureCitation>
). Posterior fins 25.8% of body length and 1.2 times longer than anterior fins. Starting points of posterior fins 62.6% and ending points of posterior fins 88.4% of body length, respectively. Posterior fins separated from anterior fins and partially rayed. Caudal fin roughly round-triangle shaped, completely rayed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. A Ferosagitta robusta (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704202" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">18C</figureCitation>
). Seminal vesicles pear-shaped with elongated posterior trunk and anterior roundish knob and touching both posterior and caudal fins. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. A Ferosagitta robusta (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704202" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">18A, C</figureCitation>
). Conspicuous intestinal diverticula present (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Number and shape of dentition A Ferosagitta robusta (two rows) B Krohnitta subtilis (one row)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704193" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">9A</figureCitation>
). Eggs reached anterior of ventral ganglion. Corona ciliata beginning behind eyes and expanding to anterior of trunk (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. A Ferosagitta robusta (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704202" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">18A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
